Package: synthetica
Title: Simulate Synthetic Datasets with Preserved Marginals and Correlation Structure
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "David A.",
           family = "Hughes",
           email = "hughes.evoanth@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Generate privacy-preserving synthetic copies of mixed-type tabular
    datasets via a Gaussian copula model. Marginal distributions (means, SDs,
    proportions, missingness) and joint correlation structure of the input are
    preserved without retaining row-level information. Optionally inject
    synthetic phenotype columns with user-specified marginal and effect size on
    a chosen subset of features.
URL: https://hughesevoanth.github.io/synthetica/, https://github.com/hughesevoanth/synthetica
BugReports: https://github.com/hughesevoanth/synthetica/issues
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
